[{"id":"VH925566","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a graph of a firm’s long run average total cost curve, abbreviated as the L R A T C curve. The horizontal axis is labeled Output, and from left to right, quantities Q sub 0 and Q sub 1 are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled Cost. The L R A T C curve begins slightly to the right of, and approximately halfway up, the vertical axis. It moves downward and to the right, steeply at first, and then begins to level out as it reaches a point directly above Q sub 0. It then moves to the right, parallel to the horizontal axis, from Q sub 0 to Q sub 1. It then moves upward and to the right, gradually at first and then more steeply, until it ends above the right side of the horizontal axis at approximately the same height as its starting point.\" height=\"189\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH925566.g03.png\" width=\"250\" /></div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The graph above shows a firm’s long-run average total cost curve <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, L R A T C, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, L R A T C, close parenthesis\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>(</mo><mtext>LRATC</mtext><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following statements is true as the firm increases its scale of production?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH925566_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">From zero output to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 0\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, the firm experiences diseconomies of scale.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">From <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 0\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 1\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, the firm experiences increasing returns to scale.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">For output levels above <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 1\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, the firm experiences diseconomies of scale.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">At all output levels, the firm’s long-run marginal cost must be constant.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">From <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 0\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 1\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L R A T C\"><math alttext=\"L R A T C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>LRATC</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> falls because average fixed cost decreases; after <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 1\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>,  <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L R A T C\"><math alttext=\"L R A T C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>LRATC</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> rises due to diminishing returns to labor.</p>"],"answer":2}]